{"word":"ἐπιχειρέω","slug":"ἐπιχειρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιχειρέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χείρ'><el>χείρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to put one's hand on</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to put one's hand to</i> a work, <i>set to work at, attempt</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:—rarely <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be attempted</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to endeavour</i> or <i>attempt to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to make an attempt on, to set upon, attack</i>, <el>τινί</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <el>πρός τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>;—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}